<F P=106> [Article by I. A. Morozov, Yu. V. Snytkin; UDC </F>
621.396.965:621.391.26] 
  [Abstract]Control using the information function involves a 
ratio analysis after each observation interval in order to 
determine the component amount of information which can provide 
the greatest increase when the controlling parameter values are 
next selected. This means a practical selection of a detection 
mode (detection, tracking, identification) and of controlling 
parameter values which can be changed in real time. When the 
loss function is not specified, control can be found and 
satisfactory results can be obtained using an approach based on 
maximizing the increase in the amount of information at each 
step. 1 figures and 2 references. 


